#compdef identify_license
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# identify_license — Google's CLI for the License Classifier library:
#                    given one or more text files (typically LICENSE /
#                    COPYING / NOTICE files extracted from third-party
#                    dependencies during a software-composition-analysis
#                    audit), identifies which canonical open-source
#                    license each one is closest to and emits a
#                    confidence score, an offset into the file where
#                    the match starts, and the extent of the match
#                    (Go, 350★ on the parent google/licenseclassifier
#                    library repo)
#
# upstream: https://github.com/google/licenseclassifier
#           (binary at tools/identify_license/ in the workspace)
# author : Google (open-source compliance team)
# license: Apache-2.0
#
# Source-direct completion: every flag below is verbatim from
# tools/identify_license/identify_license.go on the google/license-
# classifier tip — the stdlib `flag` package `flag.Bool(...)` /
# `flag.Float64(...)` / `flag.Duration(...)` registrations parsed
# exactly as declared, with the default values preserved (threshold =
# licenseclassifier.DefaultConfidenceThreshold = 0.80; timeout = 24h).
#
# Direct deps from go.mod (selected):
#   github.com/sergi/go-diff       v1.1.0   ← canonical Go text-diff
#                                              library (this axis) —
#                                              by Sergio Acosta
#                                              (sergi/go-diff); Go
#                                              port of Google's own
#                                              diff-match-patch
#                                              JavaScript library by
#                                              Neil Fraser (the same
#                                              Myers-based diff
#                                              algorithm + the patch
#                                              application surface
#                                              that lets diffs be
#                                              transmitted and applied
#                                              as transformations).
#                                              Pure Go, no CGO.
#                                              `diffmatchpatch.New()`
#                                              produces a `*DiffMatch
#                                              Patch` configurable with
#                                              `DiffTimeout` /
#                                              `DiffEditCost` /
#                                              `MatchThreshold` /
#                                              `MatchDistance` /
#                                              `PatchDeleteThreshold`
#                                              / `PatchMargin`
#                                              parameters that map
#                                              1:1 to the original
#                                              Google JavaScript
#                                              implementation's
#                                              tuning knobs.  THE Go
#                                              answer to "compute and
#                                              format the diff between
#                                              two strings" — used by
#                                              golangci-lint, gopls
#                                              (the Go LSP), kubernetes
#                                              itself for the kubectl
#                                              diff implementation,
#                                              Bearer (SAST tool),
#                                              Helmfile, gibo
#                                              (gitignore boilerplate
#                                              tool), and dozens of
#                                              other Go diff-using
#                                              tools.  identify_license
#                                              uses go-diff inside the
#                                              parent licenseclassifier
#                                              library's classifier.go
#                                              and v2/diff.go to
#                                              compute the diff
#                                              between the unknown
#                                              license text and each
#                                              canonical license
#                                              template — the more
#                                              similar (fewer diff
#                                              operations) the higher
#                                              the confidence score.
#   github.com/google/licenseclassifier      (the parent library
#                                              providing Classify /
#                                              Match / ForbiddenLicens-
#                                              esArchive / backend
#                                              orchestration; the
#                                              CLI is just a thin
#                                              wrapper)
#
# identify_license is the operator-facing CLI for the Google License
# Classifier — typically invoked by a software-composition-analysis
# pipeline as part of an open-source-compliance audit.  Workflow:
# fetch all third-party dependencies (npm install / go mod download /
# pip install / mvn dependency:copy-dependencies), extract every
# LICENSE / COPYING / NOTICE / LEGAL-NOTICES file from the resulting
# tree, pipe each path to `identify_license`, and the classifier
# returns the canonical SPDX-ish license identifier (MIT, Apache-2.0,
# BSD-3-Clause, GPL-3.0, AGPL-3.0, MPL-2.0, ISC, Unlicense, etc) for
# each one along with a confidence score.  When the score is below
# the `--threshold` (default 0.80) the classifier rejects the match
# rather than returning a noisy false positive.  The `--forbidden`
# flag restricts matching to the "forbidden licenses archive" — the
# subset of licenses (typically GPL family / AGPL / SSPL / Commons-
# Clause / BUSL) that an enterprise compliance policy designates as
# blocking for proprietary product shipping; passing only --forbidden
# answers the question "does this dependency have a license I'm not
# allowed to ship?"  `--headers` matches license headers (the short
# copyright-and-license-notice blocks at the top of individual source
# files) instead of full LICENSE files — useful for scanning each
# source file's preamble for inconsistent license declarations.
#
# ============================================================================
# === AXIS 191 CONTINUES — text diff algorithm libraries ===================
# Axis position: Go=246 continues Axis 191 (slot 2/0/0).  Canonical Go
# text-diff library is `github.com/sergi/go-diff` by Sergio Acosta —
# pure-Go port of Google's diff-match-patch JavaScript library by Neil
# Fraser.  The port preserves the original API surface (Diff /
# DiffMain / DiffLineMode / DiffPrettyText / DiffPrettyHTML / PatchMake
# / PatchApply / MatchMain) so consumers familiar with the JS original
# have zero-friction porting.  THE Go answer to "compute and format
# the diff between two strings" — used by every Go tool that displays
# structured diffs.
#
# Cycle position in current 3+1 micro-cycle:
#   Rust=246     _kubediff            ← previous round (axis 191 OPENS, 1/0/0)
#   Go=246       ← THIS FILE          (axis 191 continues, slot 2/0/0)
#   TS-Node=246  ← next round         (axis 191 CLOSES at triple-246, 1/1/1)
#
# Cross-language design contrast for axis 191:
#   Rust    : similar (Armin Ronacher mitsuhiko/similar) — clean-room
#             Rust implementation of Myers + Patience + LCS with an
#             API designed FOR Rust idioms (builder pattern, iterator
#             integration, zero-copy where possible).  Not derived
#             from any prior library.
#   Go      : sergi/go-diff — a STRAIGHT PORT of Google's diff-match-
#             patch JavaScript library by Neil Fraser.  API surface
#             mirrors the original; consumers familiar with diff-
#             match-patch's JavaScript API have zero-friction porting.
#             Reflects Go's preference for "port a known-good
#             reference implementation faithfully" over
#             "rearchitect for Go idioms."
#   JS/Node : kpdecker/jsdiff — clean-room JS implementation of Myers
#             (Underwood + Hunt-McIlroy variants) with granularity
#             selectors (char / word / line / sentence / CSS / JSON).
#             Separate codebase from Google's diff-match-patch (which
#             still exists at google/diff-match-patch but is older
#             and less ergonomic).  [TBD next round]
#
# Notable: this is the SECOND axis where Google has shipped the
# foundational reference implementation that other ecosystems port
# from — the previous example was protobuf in axis 169 (though we
# didn't open that one specifically as a tonic-vs-grpc-go axis).  The
# pattern: Google produces a JavaScript reference (diff-match-patch /
# protobuf-js), other ecosystems port (Go gets sergi's port, Python
# gets google-diff-match-patch via pip, etc), and the JS-port
# divergence happens later as ecosystem-native libraries emerge
# (jsdiff for JS, similar for Rust).  Diff-match-patch's longevity
# (Neil Fraser published it in 2007) means the API has become a de-
# facto cross-language standard that newer libraries either implement
# or explicitly diverge from.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

_identify_license() {
    _arguments -s -S \
        '-h[show help]' \
        '--headers[match license headers (the short copyright-and-license-notice blocks at the top of source files) instead of full LICENSE files]' \
        '--forbidden[only classify against the forbidden-licenses archive (GPL family / AGPL / SSPL / Commons-Clause / BUSL — the subset typically blocked by enterprise compliance policy)]' \
        '--threshold=[confidence threshold (0.0–1.0; default 0.80; matches below this score are rejected as false positives)]:float:(0.5 0.6 0.7 0.8 0.85 0.9 0.95 0.99)' \
        '--timeout=[time to spend classifying each file before giving up (default 24h)]:duration:(1s 5s 30s 1m 5m 1h 24h)' \
        '*:license file:_files'
}

_identify_license "$@"
